{
  "stem": "6052.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "It was just a small knapsack on our-- on my back.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "That was all.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "All what we had was either taken away or destroyed by the Nazis.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So can you imagine a family of five persons-- three sisters, two brothers, two parents-- and an additional family of my grandmother and my uncle and my-- my aunts.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That nothing-- nothing but nothing remained, and that we were just with our naked body-- naked body-- forced to leave.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And this was, of course, even better than to be destroyed.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And about the part of destruction, I will tell you now.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We, my brother and I, were in a group which was formed by the Israelitische Religionsgemeinde sent to Zagreb.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And this was an adventure.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But we felt it more than adventure than kind of strict rescue mission.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But it was apparently necessary.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Before we were sent, we met-- oh!",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "My mother, may she rest in peace, was the one who accompanied us to the Israelitische Religionsgemeinde, where we could say goodbye.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And from there it was then to the Leipziger Hauptbahnhof, where my brother and I and other 12 youngsters would be going to the annexed Austria, which was then Vienna, and from Vienna to Graz.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But it was a heartbreaking time, because my mother-- we saw her the last time at that point.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was the most heartbreaking time-- time at our life, to knowingly separate from her that-- with the knowledge that it is not-- most probably not going to be a soon reunification.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Also, we tried to believe that there will be a reunification.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But we knew that things became so bad that it might not happen.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And so we said goodbye-- Auf Wiedersehen-- at that time.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We kissed.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And whenever I come back to that point, I shudder.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
